    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-12T19:12:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-12T19:12:00-05:00" n="77"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d77">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–1251: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">Embassy in Greece</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d77fn1">Repeated for information to Paris priority as <gloss
                            target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 430.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <gloss target="#t_niact1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">niact</hi>
                        </gloss>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-12T19:12:00-05:00"
                            >December 12, 1951—7:12 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2827. Re <gloss target="#t_urtel1">urtel</gloss> 2728. While we appreciate
                    Greeks’ discomfiture over <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> election
                    developments, we hope you will make it clear to them <pb facs="0147" n="125"
                        xml:id="pg_125"/> that decision whether continue in race is matter for their
                    own determination. There shld be no misunderstanding re fact they decided on
                    their own to make race and US support was given only after Greece seemed leading
                    non-Soviet candidate.</p>
                <p>We expect <gloss target="#t_GADel1">GADel</gloss> will inform <gloss
                        target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss> re prospects in Dec 13 balloting. Seems to us
                    Greeks shld pick up number of <gloss target="#t_LA1">LA</gloss> votes, and
                    perhaps UK and Fr votes on second ballot as well. If <gloss target="#t_GADel1"
                        >GADel</gloss> concurs, you may inform Greeks our own view wld therefore be
                    that they wld be wise reserve decision re withdrawal until several more ballots
                    cast. We repeat, however, Greeks must make this decision themselves.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
